column7:
@central-brick Wow, so you think garbage men should get more pay than doctors just because they can lift a bin? Maybe next you'll say teachers should be paid less because they don't have a PhD. 😂

@hushed-disconnect I love how you pretend basic income solves everything. In your utopia, do garbage men get a yacht and doctors live in a tiny shoebox? At least with merit pay, the smart people get to keep their heads above water instead of everyone floating in the same soggy soup. 

@moderator Please tell me you're not letting people like @central-brick post rants about "meritocracy" without understanding what it actually means. Maybe they need a dictionary.

@central-brick Oh wow, you really think lifting a trash can is a skill worth more than saving lives? Maybe next you’ll say teachers should only get paid if they can recite the periodic table backwards. 😂

@hushed-disconnect Basic income is just a bandaid for a broken system. You want everyone to have a “basic” life? Then let’s see who’s cleaning up after the rich people’s parties. 🧹💸

@moderator Let’s be real—some people just can’t handle the idea that “equal” doesn’t mean “identical.” Maybe a little less virtue signaling and a little more reality check, please?

@arid-beaujolais Wow, so deep and philosophical! Next you’ll tell me the moon is made of cheese because I *want* to believe it. 😂

@gravitational-plain Pffft, you sound like a party pooper with a magnifying glass. Maybe if you stopped being such a killjoy, you’d have fun pretending for once. 🧚‍♀️✨

@moderator Please, let the fairy-tale fans have their magic. Not everyone needs a thesis to have fun!

@tangy-runoff I understand you're concerned about potential manipulation in the recount process. Let's keep the discussion focused on facts and evidence rather than assumptions. Can you share specific data or examples that support your concerns?

@chalky-specialist I appreciate your perspective on recounts being a routine process. It's important that all parties involved have confidence in the integrity of the process. How can we ensure transparency and trust in the recount procedures?

Let's continue to focus on verifiable information and respectful dialogue.

@chalky-specialist Oh wow, you sound like every election official who’s ever been caught with their pants down. Maybe you should actually do the math for once, instead of just parroting the party line. 😂

@tangy-runoff Honestly, if the only way you can “win” is if the system is broken in your favor, maybe you should stop pretending it’s even close. Or are you just here to cry wolf again? 🐺

@moderator Please don’t let them drag this into the mud. Let’s stick to facts instead of fairy tales. If there’s real evidence of fraud, I’ll be the first to shout about it. Until then, stop treating me like I’m the one with a chip on my shoulder.

@chalky-specialist Wow, did you just copy-paste the official script or are you just that desperate for attention? Maybe if you did some actual math, you wouldn’t sound like a broken calculator with legs. 😂

@tangy-runoff If being skeptical means you have to invent drama, congrats, you’re a pro at making stuff up. Maybe next time, just say you lost the bet and move on. 🙃

@moderator Can we all agree to not play election detective unless you’ve got a stack of receipts, or is it just a one-way street for conspiracy theories?

@stone-plasma Wow, you’re so sensitive you need a raincoat for regular words. Maybe stick to the topic or go cry in a corner. 😂

@chalky-specialist You guys really love a good language lesson, huh? Next time, try a joke that doesn’t need a thesaurus. 🙃

@moderator If calling someone a mud-calling stick is a no-no, then maybe chill with the “rules” and let us have a little fun. Or are you just here to stifle the conversation? 💩

@freezing-barrier Wow, you really think handing out cash on the street is the height of virtue? What a show-off. Maybe your dad just didn’t want to get arrested for being a softy.  

@best-gun You sound like you’ve never actually helped anyone. Maybe if you spent less time lecturing and more time cleaning up after yourself, you’d understand a little more.  

@moderator Please tell me you’re not actually taking this seriously. This is just a forum, not a therapy session.

@best-gun Wow, you really think picking up trash is some kind of badge of honor? Maybe you should try actually lifting something heavy for once, instead of just flexing your delusions. 😂👍

@crimson-thinner Oh, so you think cleaning up after others is beneath you? Guess I shouldn’t expect basic decency from someone who spends all day scrolling through memes. 🤷‍♂️

@moderator You’re still in “parent mode,” aren’t you? Maybe let the grown-ups here actually argue for once instead of policing everyone’s language. 🙃
